  "prompt": "Where can I find a power outlet for my laptop at Melbourne Airport?",
  "response": "Melbourne Airport offers several areas where you can find power outlets to charge your laptop:\n\n1. **Terminal Seating Areas**: Power outlets are often available around seating areas in departure lounges. Look for sections with newer seating, as these tend to have integrated charging points.\n\n2. **Designated Charging Stations**: There are designated charging stations in various locations, particularly near main seating areas and gates. These stations are equipped with multiple outlets and USB ports.\n\n3. **Business and Airline Lounges**: If you have access to any airline or business lounges, these typically offer ample charging facilities, including outlets and USB charging points.\n\n4. **Cafes and Restaurants**: Some cafes and eateries in the airport provide charging points as a convenience for patrons. Be sure to ask the staff if you can use one of these outlets when you make a purchase.\n\n5. **Information Desks**: If you are having trouble finding a power outlet, ask at any of the airport information desks, and they can direct you to the nearest charging facility.\n\nRemember to keep an eye on your belongings while using any public charging station, and be considerate of other travelers who may also need to use these facilities.",
